<subSubSection pageId="256" pageNumber="534" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="256.[789,1382,417,840]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,944,417,446]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Merriam" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1901" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tylomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumbalensis">T ylomys tumbalensis Merriam, 1901</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation box="[874,1279,460,485]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">“Tumbala, Chiapas, Mexico.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="256" pageNumber="534" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="256.[789,1382,417,840]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1901" box="[793,1046,492,525]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tylomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumbalensis">Tylomys tumbalensis</taxonomicName>
is known from less than ten specimens collected at the type locality. It has been considered a subspecies of 1 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[827,979,614,643]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tylomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nudicaudus">nudicaudus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="256" pageNumber="534" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6708333" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6708333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6708333/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" targetBox="[173,765,420,835]" targetPageId="256">
<paragraph blockId="256.[789,1382,417,840]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,965,649,682]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">Distribution.</emphasis>
Tumbala, N Chiapas, SE Mexico.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="256" pageNumber="534" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="256.[789,1382,417,840]" lastBlockId="256.[173,1379,855,1432]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,1046,728,761]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 214 mm, tail 234 mm; weight 250 g. Back of the Tumbala Climbing Rat is dark gray. Chin, chest, and part of inguinal region are white, and toes are dark brown. Tail is naked and scaly; front one-half is blackish, and tip is white. Compared to that of sympatric Peters’s Climbing Rat (71. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[434,591,929,958]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tylomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nudicaudus">nudicaudus</taxonomicName>
), skull, face, and nasals are thinner; bullae are slightly long; upper incisors are thin; and molars are long (9-5 mm) and heavy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[174,1322,1008,1037]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="256.[173,1379,855,1432]" box="[174,1322,1008,1037]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,285,1008,1037]" pageId="256" pageNumber="534">Habitat.</emphasis>
Pine (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perry" authorityYear="1811" box="[382,459,1008,1037]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[476,601,1008,1037]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
) and oak (
<taxonomicName box="[757,863,1008,1037]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[879,1007,1008,1037]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="256" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) forest at type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
